re’s presence at home, in metropolitan scenes of fashionable sociability. Combining literary studies and new imperial history, Cohen demonstrates how the imaginative geography of the Indies shaped the culture of British imperialism, which then changed the shape of the world.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 01. Dez 2022) 0aGreat Britain-Colonies-History-18th century. 0aHistory, Moderny18th century. 0aHistory, Moderny19th century. 0aImperialism in popular culture-Great Britain-18th century. 0aImperialism. 0aSlaveryzWest Indies, British. 7aHISTORY / Europe / Great Britain / Georgian Era (1714-1837).2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishz978311070471608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020z9783110704518oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE History 2020 Englishz978311070473008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE History 2020z9783110704525oZDB-23-DEG40uhttps://doi.org/10.12987/9780300255690?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300255690423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780300255690/original  a978-3-11-070471-6  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishb2020  a978-3-11-070473-0  EBOOK PACKAGE History 2020 Englishb2020  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-DEGb2020  aZDB-23-DGGb2020  aZDB-23-UCY